!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

surrender /səˈrɛndə/

(surrendering,surrendered,surrenders) 

1. V-I If you surrender , you stop fighting or resisting someone and agree that you have been beaten. 投降; 屈服 

例： General Martin Bonnet called on the rebels to surrender. 马丁·邦尼特将军要求反叛分子们投降。 

2. N-VAR Surrender is also a noun. 投降; 屈服 

例： ...the government's apparent surrender to demands made by the religious militants. …政府对宗教好战分子所提要求的明显屈从。 

3. V-T If you surrender something you would rather keep, you give it up or let someone else have it, for example after a struggle. 放弃; 交出 

例： Nadja had to fill out forms surrendering all rights to her property. 纳贾不得不填写表格，放弃对她财产的所有权利。 

4. N-UNCOUNT Surrender is also a noun. 放弃; 交出 

例： ...the sixteen-day deadline for the surrender of weapons and ammunition. …交出武器弹药的16天期限。 

5. V-T If you surrender something such as a ticket or your passport, you give it to someone in authority when they ask you to. 交出 [正式] 

例： They have been ordered to surrender their passports. 他们已被命令交出他们的护照。

</div>

